===Adjective===
'''cold''' ({compar}} '''[[colder]]''', {{superl}} '''[[coldest]]''')

#Having a low [[temperature]].
#:''A cold wind whistled through the trees.''
#Unfriendly, emotionally distant or unfeeling.
#:''She shot me a cold glance before turning her back.''
#Completely [[unprepared]].
#:''The speaker went in cold and floundered for a topic.''

====Synonyms====
*(''having a low temperature''): [[chilled]], [[chilly]], [[freezing]], [[frigid]], [[glacial]], [[icy]]
**(''specifically, of the weather''): (''all British slang''): [[brass monkeys]], [[nippy]], [[parky]], [[taters]]
*(''unfriendly''): [[aloof]], [[distant]], [[hostile]], [[standoffish]], [[unfriendly]], [[unwelcoming]]
*(''unprepared''): [[unprepared]], [[unready]]

====Antonyms====
*(''having a low temperature''): [[baking]], [[boiling]], [[heated]], [[hot]], [[scorching]], [[searing]], [[torrid]], [[warm]]
